1
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:23,533
Yeah.

2
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:26,267
Of course I got it.
What do you think?

3
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:29,633
Two shots,
and two more to be sure.

4
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:31,067
I haven't had a chance
to read it yet,

5
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:33,400
but whatever toulon's hiding,

6
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:35,900
this looks like a great place
to find it.

7
00:01:37,067 --> 00:01:40,733
I told you,
satisfaction guaranteed.

8
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,633
I'll ring you back.

9
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:50,067
Ok, puppet master,
tell me everything.

10
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:55,167
Man: It all began, I suppose,

11
00:01:55,233 --> 00:02:01,167
one day with old afzel...
In Cairo...

12
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:03,100
Long ago.

13
00:02:04,433 --> 00:02:06,600
[Indistinct chatter]

14
00:02:17,567 --> 00:02:20,500
The most
sensational secret
the sands have revealed

15
00:02:20,567 --> 00:02:24,433
since the unholy
desecration of
ramses' tomb.

16
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:25,967
Look.

17
00:02:26,067 --> 00:02:28,133
Already the electrical
marvels of the present

18
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:31,433
cast a cruel light
upon their deficiency.

19
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:39,600
Dead end.

20
00:02:39,667 --> 00:02:41,233
The formula's not here.

21
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:45,333
No, no one's getting it.
Toulon made sure of that.

22
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:47,900
Well, we'll just
move to phase two.

23
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:18,633
Man:
Don't worry.

24
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:22,933
You won't be defenseless
for long.

25
00:03:23,067 --> 00:03:26,067
It looks like you two
are not gonna give me
any trouble.

26
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:27,300
What is this?

27
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:29,600
This is a robbery,
Mr. hirst.

28
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:33,200
Then you'll be disappointed.
I'm not a rich man.

29
00:03:33,267 --> 00:03:35,867
But you can take
anything you want.

30
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:37,700
I have a set
of wine glasses
in the dining room

31
00:03:37,767 --> 00:03:39,933
that might fetch you
a few dollars.

32
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:41,833
I don't give a damn
about that shit,

33
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:42,967
and you know it.

34
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:44,600
The only thing
I'm interested in

35
00:03:44,667 --> 00:03:47,067
is the only thing
of value you have,

36
00:03:47,067 --> 00:03:49,167
and that's
Andre toulon's formula

37
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:52,100
for bringing
these creatures to life.

38
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:53,600
Again, you'll be
disappointed.

39
00:03:53,667 --> 00:03:56,067
Don't test me.

40
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:58,800
You're very good
with a gun, I'm sure.

41
00:03:58,867 --> 00:04:01,767
But you just want
something I don't have.

42
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:04,067
This looks like
the right place.

43
00:04:04,067 --> 00:04:06,067
No. I knew toulon,

44
00:04:06,067 --> 00:04:09,133
but he never
confided in me.

45
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,867
You want the collector
that bought his diary.

46
00:04:11,933 --> 00:04:13,567
I have his address.

47
00:04:13,633 --> 00:04:15,367
Yeah, I know that man.

48
00:04:15,433 --> 00:04:19,300
I killed him 6 hours ago,
and the diary is worthless.

49
00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:21,133
You want to try again?

50
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,967
I've dealt with
your type before.

51
00:04:23,067 --> 00:04:24,900
Don't screw with me,
old man.

52
00:04:24,967 --> 00:04:26,567
I want that formula.

53
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:27,967
I can't give it to you.

54
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:30,633
It's not
some instant recipe
I can just hand over.

55
00:04:30,700 --> 00:04:32,367
It's more complicated
than that.

56
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:34,100
Really?

57
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:35,933
Aah! Ohh.

58
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:42,933
You don't know
how high the stakes are

59
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:45,633
or how far I'll go.

60
00:04:46,533 --> 00:04:48,633
I'll do what I can.

61
00:04:53,067 --> 00:04:55,733
I'll give you
whatever toulon left me.

62
00:04:58,133 --> 00:05:00,067
Everything he wanted me
to know,

63
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,867
in his own voice.

64
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,400
This better
be something.

65
00:05:07,467 --> 00:05:09,067
It will be.

66
00:05:12,167 --> 00:05:15,667
Toulon, on tape:
Well, my friends, how are you?

67
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:22,900
Oh, don't answer that question.
I can see.

68
00:05:22,967 --> 00:05:27,600
Young and healthy, cool, calm,
collected, and contented.

69
00:05:27,667 --> 00:05:30,200
And sin should be contented.

70
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:32,767
Lonely, cosseted lives...

71
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,500
You're carried
from adventure to adventure

72
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:36,933
in your warm, comfortable trunk,

73
00:05:37,067 --> 00:05:38,733
and who carries you?

74
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:42,967
I do... a frail, fragile old man.

75
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:44,733
But I'm going to alter that.

76
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,967
Next time,
we'll cut off your feet,

77
00:05:48,067 --> 00:05:49,900
and I'll put you up on wheels,

78
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:53,167
and you can all
pull me along in the trunk.

79
00:05:57,767 --> 00:06:00,333
Well.

80
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:03,667
Cyclops.

81
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:06,567
Cyclops.

82
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:09,200
He was one of the first
in the family.

83
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,200
[Drum roll]

84
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:24,633
Ladies and gentlemen,

85
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:27,667
I would like to welcome you
to the real world...

86
00:06:27,733 --> 00:06:31,967
A world of magic,
of gods, and of monsters.

87
00:06:32,067 --> 00:06:35,933
Here, all familiar illusion
will be swept away.

88
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:39,967
Here, all things become one.

89
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:46,367
Terror and wonder,
heaven and hell,

90
00:06:46,433 --> 00:06:50,067
fear and desire.

91
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:55,867
I give you the theatre majic,
where all things are possible.

92
00:07:13,067 --> 00:07:14,933
[Music playing]

93
00:07:23,267 --> 00:07:26,333
With this one eye of mine,

94
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,667
I can see better
than any other two.

95
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,833
If one is better than two,

96
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:40,533
then perhaps none
would be better than one.

97
00:07:45,067 --> 00:07:48,333
What strange and frightening
place is this?

98
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:53,367
Don't you know,
my friend?

99
00:07:53,433 --> 00:07:58,467
Smell the sulfur.
Feel the heat
of the flames.

100
00:07:59,567 --> 00:08:03,667
We could be
nowhere else but hell.

101
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:07,067
Everywhere is hell,
for we are the damned.

102
00:08:09,467 --> 00:08:12,467
There is no escape
from fate.

103
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:15,300
We are all puppets
dancing on a string.

104
00:08:15,367 --> 00:08:17,967
Free will is an illusion.

105
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:21,900
We can only act
at the whim
of the puppeteer.

106
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:24,433
Then our path is clear...

107
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:27,433
In the defying of toulon,
and with me as well.

108
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:30,867
And thus the comedy ends.

109
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:32,633
[People gasp]

110
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,633
[Applause]

111
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,467
I saw you in the theatre.

112
00:08:39,533 --> 00:08:41,567
And I saw you.

113
00:08:41,633 --> 00:08:44,133
Um... That is,
of course,

114
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:47,433
I saw you, ah...
Uh...

115
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,067
Have you been
doing this for long...

116
00:08:49,133 --> 00:08:50,733
The puppets, I mean?

117
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,133
All my life.

118
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,167
Really?

119
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:57,333
Take it.

120
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,767
The tool of the art,
I give it to you.

121
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,633
Careful.

122
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:34,067
The ring
does not matter.

123
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:37,567
It has no special power.
It is merely a tool.

124
00:09:37,633 --> 00:09:40,367
The same is true
with the fluid.

125
00:09:40,433 --> 00:09:42,067
For our magic,

126
00:09:42,067 --> 00:09:45,233
it serves
merely as a bridge...

127
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:49,533
For the life force,
for the soul.

128
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,233
Now...

129
00:10:05,767 --> 00:10:08,067
Now the words.

130
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:14,567
[Chanting
in foreign language]

131
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:40,033
With experience,
as you grow stronger,

132
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,867
you will not have to
say the words out loud.

133
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:45,600
To think them
will be enough.

134
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:51,000
There. See?

135
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,300
See?

136
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:25,800
It cannot speak,
of course, but it lives.

137
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:28,133
It lives.

138
00:11:29,467 --> 00:11:32,467
The secret of reanimation
wasn't safe.

139
00:11:32,533 --> 00:11:35,167
My enemies wanted it
and would do anything,

140
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:38,633
including kidnap my fiance, to
get it.

141
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,833
But there was no way
I was going to let her be hurt

142
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:42,533
because of me.

143
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:45,567
And, thank god... or the devil...

144
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:48,633
My little friends
felt the same way.

145
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:39,367
[Grunting]

146
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:13,700
Come forward.

147
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:15,633
[Laughing]

148
00:13:37,067 --> 00:13:39,367
[Grunting]

149
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,700
[Thud]

150
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:27,067
[Train whistle blowing]

151
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:35,233
That's it?

152
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:37,067
I don't give a damn
about this drivel...

153
00:15:37,067 --> 00:15:39,333
The puppet master lived
happily ever after.

154
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:42,800
But he didn't.
He became a fugitive.

155
00:15:42,867 --> 00:15:45,400
Don't you know anything
about Andre toulon?

156
00:15:45,467 --> 00:15:47,133
I know he had a secret,

157
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,967
and I know that
he passed it on to you

158
00:15:49,067 --> 00:15:52,433
and that could be
your death sentence.

159
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:54,433
The fluid is over there
in that vial.

160
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,833
Take it
and have it analyzed.

161
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:56,933
I won't object.

162
00:15:57,067 --> 00:15:59,600
Dozens have tried,
and dozens have died.

163
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:03,233
The missing element
is in this room
with you.

164
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:06,133
No, it's still with him.

165
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,233
Look, I know you
can kill me at any moment,

166
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:10,567
but I really am
trying to help.

167
00:16:10,633 --> 00:16:12,967
If you knew Andre toulon,
knew his history,

168
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:16,733
then you'd know the secret
to sustaining eternal life.

169
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:22,767
I think he always
regretted his discovery.

170
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:24,167
Why?

171
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:26,867
It could have made him
the most powerful man
in the world.

172
00:16:26,933 --> 00:16:28,500
Instead,
it made him a fugitive.

173
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:31,133
He spent his life running.

174
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,433
When I first met him,
he was still happy,

175
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,433
doing what he loved to do...

176
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:38,767
Being puppet master
to a theater full of children.

177
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:41,300
[Laughter]

178
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,667
[Applause]

179
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:51,900
I never know
what they're
going to do or say.

180
00:16:51,967 --> 00:16:54,233
They may hide
in your pocket.

181
00:16:55,467 --> 00:16:57,167
You have been stealing.

182
00:16:57,233 --> 00:16:58,633
Father,
I didn't steal it.

183
00:16:58,700 --> 00:16:59,667
Peppermints.

184
00:16:59,733 --> 00:17:01,233
Peppermints
everywhere. Look.

185
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:03,133
It's a good job
you put plenty of candy

186
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,533
into Peter's pocket,

187
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:06,233
or he might have been
very angry with you,

188
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,233
mightn't we, Peter?

189
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:09,733
I would forgive him.

190
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,733
All right, children.

191
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:11,967
Now, the puppets
are very tired.

192
00:17:12,067 --> 00:17:14,100
They must go to bed now.

193
00:17:14,167 --> 00:17:17,067
Sleep?
Puppets need to sleep?

194
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:20,300
Puppets need sleep
just as much as you do.

195
00:17:20,367 --> 00:17:21,367
Good-bye.

196
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:23,700
Please come back
and see us again. Soon.

197
00:17:23,767 --> 00:17:25,233
Danke, herr toulon.

198
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:28,067
Come, Peter.
Come children.

199
00:17:28,067 --> 00:17:30,133
Come, come.

200
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:32,067
[Children murmuring]

201
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,667
Peter.

202
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:53,367
You have a devoted audience,
herr toulon.

203
00:17:53,433 --> 00:17:55,467
And I am devoted
to them.

204
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:57,867
They love your puppets.

205
00:17:57,933 --> 00:17:59,500
The children
enjoy the show,

206
00:17:59,567 --> 00:18:01,400
and I am rewarded
by their laughter,

207
00:18:01,467 --> 00:18:03,067
which is honest.

208
00:18:03,133 --> 00:18:05,867
It's not always prudent.

209
00:18:08,233 --> 00:18:10,267
I wonder if
they'd laugh so hard

210
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:13,067
if they truly understood
what they were watching.

211
00:18:13,067 --> 00:18:14,733
Oh, I'm sure
they would.

212
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:19,567
Political satire
is one of the marks
of a healthy society.

213
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:21,633
I didn't get your name.

214
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:24,700
Lieutenant Eric Stein.

215
00:18:24,767 --> 00:18:27,200
Fellow puppeteer.

216
00:18:27,267 --> 00:18:28,367
I've been carving
marionettes

217
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:29,867
since I was 10 years old,

218
00:18:29,933 --> 00:18:33,300
and I must say your
craftsmanship is superb.

219
00:18:33,367 --> 00:18:35,733
You are very kind,
lieutenant.

220
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,700
How do you
manipulate them
without string works?

221
00:18:38,767 --> 00:18:42,600
Authorization.
It is my own method.

222
00:18:42,667 --> 00:18:45,700
Stein: The show itself
is a disgusting
burlesque of the fuhrer

223
00:18:45,767 --> 00:18:48,200
and makes a mockery
of the reich.

224
00:18:54,433 --> 00:18:57,733
Man: Yeah. Have the men
ready to leave immediately.

225
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:58,967
[Hangs up telephone]

226
00:18:59,067 --> 00:19:02,200
Sir,
there's something else.

227
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:03,767
Yeah?

228
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:08,767
Lieutenant...
What is this?

229
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:09,933
I may be wrong,

230
00:19:10,067 --> 00:19:13,200
but it seems as though
these wooden figures are...

231
00:19:13,267 --> 00:19:15,067
Walking about
on their own.

232
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:18,067
You're not mistaken,
sir.

233
00:19:23,667 --> 00:19:24,600
Well.

234
00:19:24,667 --> 00:19:26,833
[Chuckling

235
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:30,900
explain this.

236
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:33,567
I really can't, sir.

237
00:19:33,633 --> 00:19:38,267
Herr toulon has developed
a method of animating
his puppets without string.

238
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:39,367
He claimed
they were motorized,

239
00:19:39,433 --> 00:19:41,633
but it's much more
than that.

240
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:44,533
I... I've seen them walk,

241
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:47,600
react to sound
as if they could hear.

242
00:19:47,667 --> 00:19:49,700
[People marching]

243
00:19:49,767 --> 00:19:51,467
It's as if
they were alive.

244
00:19:51,533 --> 00:19:53,633
Stein...

245
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:02,600
Have you lost your senses?

246
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:05,267
It... it's the truth,
sir.

247
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,800
Just like
the real thing, huh?

248
00:20:11,867 --> 00:20:13,067
Only more intelligent.

249
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:14,400
Ha ha ha!

250
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:19,833
This theater is closed,

251
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:23,500
by the authority of
the German high command.

252
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:35,800
Your career
as an entertainer
is over, herr toulon.

253
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:38,867
This is one of
the puppets I was
telling you about.

254
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:51,833
Doctor.

255
00:20:56,867 --> 00:20:58,633
Herr toulon,

256
00:20:58,700 --> 00:21:01,767
I would like to
talk to you later
about your work.

257
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,433
Ah.

258
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:10,867
And here's...
The miracle, yeah?

259
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:12,067
Stein: That...
That's what I saw, yes.

260
00:21:12,133 --> 00:21:14,867
Well, that shouldn't be
difficult to analyze.

261
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:16,700
What we need
is the process.

262
