540
00:49:00,167 --> 00:49:03,100
They definitely
served their
purpose.

541
00:49:03,167 --> 00:49:06,733
Of course. Otherwise,
you wouldn't want
the secret so badly.

542
00:49:06,800 --> 00:49:07,967
They did something
remarkable

543
00:49:08,067 --> 00:49:10,333
because toulon
commanded them.

544
00:49:13,067 --> 00:49:15,700
Toulon: He, Ricardo, was
a bright young man,

545
00:49:15,767 --> 00:49:20,233
a scientist, the only one
who discovered my secret
and wasn't twisted by it,

546
00:49:20,300 --> 00:49:21,933
but there were other
forces at work,

547
00:49:22,067 --> 00:49:24,500
force we could never
have imagined.

548
00:49:24,567 --> 00:49:27,600
Ricardo, voice-over: I had been
a caretaker at the bodega bay
inn for the off-season,

549
00:49:27,667 --> 00:49:30,067
just me and my experiments.

550
00:49:30,067 --> 00:49:32,167
I was researching
artificial intelligence,

551
00:49:32,233 --> 00:49:35,200
trying to make my model robots
function autonomously.

552
00:49:35,267 --> 00:49:38,967
I was working for biotech,
a major scientific
industrial concern,

553
00:49:39,067 --> 00:49:42,500
with Dr. Baker
and Dr. Piper,

554
00:49:42,567 --> 00:49:44,667
but some power was unleashed,

555
00:49:44,733 --> 00:49:49,933
some awesome power that was
beyond our control,

556
00:49:50,067 --> 00:49:53,067
and after killing
Baker and Piper...

557
00:49:54,233 --> 00:49:55,167
Aah!

558
00:49:55,233 --> 00:49:56,433
It came after me.

559
00:49:56,500 --> 00:49:58,533
[Screaming]

560
00:50:01,367 --> 00:50:03,100
So you two
know each other?

561
00:50:03,167 --> 00:50:05,967
Well, you bet we do.
We go all the way back
to the institute.

562
00:50:06,033 --> 00:50:08,333
Ricardo, voice-over:
A coworker of mine
decided to visit,

563
00:50:08,400 --> 00:50:11,500
interrupting a planned weekend
with my girlfriend.

564
00:50:16,100 --> 00:50:19,833
He brought along another girl.,
a psychic,

565
00:50:19,900 --> 00:50:23,100
who right away suspected
something was wrong.

566
00:50:23,167 --> 00:50:25,667
Was she ever right.

567
00:50:25,733 --> 00:50:28,833
Mind if I sprint
through your program
here, Ricardo?

568
00:50:28,900 --> 00:50:33,067
I'd rather
you didn't.

569
00:50:33,133 --> 00:50:38,400
Come on. It's not
like I'm gonna
steal anything.

570
00:50:38,467 --> 00:50:40,200
Ricardo, voice-over:
Through her channeling,
I found a trunk in a room

571
00:50:40,267 --> 00:50:42,033
I'd never gone in,

572
00:50:42,100 --> 00:50:44,933
a trunk full of puppets,

573
00:50:45,000 --> 00:50:49,233
lifelike puppets that
had been built by Andre toulon.

574
00:50:49,300 --> 00:50:53,800
He'd escaped Nazi Germany
and come here,

575
00:50:53,867 --> 00:50:56,833
and his spirit was very present.

576
00:50:56,900 --> 00:50:58,867
He's been working
on the very equations
and theories

577
00:50:58,933 --> 00:51:00,433
that I was working on.

578
00:51:00,500 --> 00:51:07,100
He was afraid
of what they'd do
with that power.

579
00:51:07,167 --> 00:51:08,767
Ricardo, voice-over:
We found vials of substance

580
00:51:08,833 --> 00:51:15,600
that when injected
into the puppets gave them life,

581
00:51:15,667 --> 00:51:20,533
by all accounts, real life
and independent thought.

582
00:51:20,600 --> 00:51:22,133
Man: This is
so stimulating.

583
00:51:22,200 --> 00:51:23,133
It was amazing.

584
00:51:23,200 --> 00:51:24,600
Somebody pinch me.

585
00:51:24,667 --> 00:51:26,733
Aah!

586
00:51:26,800 --> 00:51:28,367
[Groaning]

587
00:51:28,433 --> 00:51:32,467
Get it off me, man!

588
00:51:32,533 --> 00:51:36,367
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

589
00:51:36,433 --> 00:51:37,667
Oh, no!

590
00:51:41,933 --> 00:51:45,067
Ricardo, voice-over:
But the evil that was trapped
in Dr. Baker and Dr. Piper

591
00:51:45,133 --> 00:51:48,200
caught up with us.

592
00:51:48,267 --> 00:51:50,467
We unleashed creatures
from the underworld

593
00:51:50,533 --> 00:51:55,067
that were after
the same secret we were.

594
00:51:55,067 --> 00:51:57,900
It was a nightmare that
I didn't believe at first,

595
00:51:57,967 --> 00:52:01,433
but as the night wore on,
I couldn't escape the truth.

596
00:52:01,500 --> 00:52:03,733
[Screaming]

597
00:52:11,100 --> 00:52:12,933
We banded together and fought.

598
00:52:13,067 --> 00:52:15,467
The puppets attacked
the creatures instinctively,

599
00:52:15,533 --> 00:52:18,167
and the spirit of toulon
guided us through the battle,

600
00:52:18,233 --> 00:52:24,067
giving us courage
and showing us the way
to defeat the beasts.

601
00:52:24,067 --> 00:52:26,233
[Screeching]

602
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:37,967
[Screeches]

603
00:52:42,167 --> 00:52:44,533
Get off her,
you little bastard!

604
00:52:46,500 --> 00:52:47,733
Aah!

605
00:52:50,567 --> 00:52:52,733
Die! Unh!

606
00:52:52,800 --> 00:52:54,867
Yes!

607
00:52:54,933 --> 00:52:57,700
Ricardo: We animated toulon's
unfinished puppet,

608
00:52:57,767 --> 00:53:01,233
decapitron, to defeat
the strongest creature.

609
00:53:11,833 --> 00:53:14,800
Ohh! Ohh!

610
00:53:14,867 --> 00:53:17,067
[Screeching]

611
00:53:26,200 --> 00:53:33,967
I think toulon and I knew
the job wasn't finished.

612
00:53:34,067 --> 00:53:36,500
I am with you.

613
00:53:36,567 --> 00:53:39,267
The power of the magic
has been set free.

614
00:53:39,333 --> 00:53:42,400
Now it needs a wise master
to channel and control it,

615
00:53:42,467 --> 00:53:44,467
to keep it from evil.

616
00:53:44,533 --> 00:53:47,833
I am with you,
puppet master.

617
00:53:47,900 --> 00:53:49,700
Woman: I know
all about that kid.

618
00:53:49,767 --> 00:53:51,333
Who do you think
took 4 bullets

619
00:53:51,400 --> 00:53:53,900
trying to keep
that diary
away from me?

620
00:53:53,967 --> 00:53:55,233
My god!

621
00:53:55,300 --> 00:53:57,800
I have to have that,

622
00:53:57,867 --> 00:54:00,800
and you better pray
that I am satisfied.

623
00:54:08,433 --> 00:54:11,200
Toulon: There was always
someone waiting to
discover my secret,

624
00:54:11,267 --> 00:54:13,600
even after my supposed death,

625
00:54:13,667 --> 00:54:15,233
always someone who didn't
have the knowledge

626
00:54:15,300 --> 00:54:18,400
to fully understand
what a gift or a curse

627
00:54:18,467 --> 00:54:21,100
the formula for the puppets
really is.

628
00:54:21,167 --> 00:54:24,067
Here. Let me introduce
you to Robert.

629
00:54:24,067 --> 00:54:26,067
Is that for real?

630
00:54:26,133 --> 00:54:27,633
Yeah. We call
this fellow pinhead.

631
00:54:27,700 --> 00:54:30,067
I mean, upstairs,
it's all just bunkum,

632
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:31,633
but these are
the real models.

633
00:54:31,700 --> 00:54:33,900
See that mean-looking
fellow there,
we call him blade.

634
00:54:33,967 --> 00:54:35,533
Don't shake his hand.

635
00:54:35,600 --> 00:54:37,300
Fellow next to him
is called six-shooter,

636
00:54:37,367 --> 00:54:38,933
and that's Jester,

637
00:54:39,067 --> 00:54:41,767
and our lovely lady
is leach woman.

638
00:54:41,833 --> 00:54:42,967
Why leach woman?

639
00:54:43,067 --> 00:54:45,800
Well, hope that
you never find out.

640
00:54:45,867 --> 00:54:50,433
And this is tunneler.
Aptly named. Ha ha!

641
00:54:50,500 --> 00:54:51,767
There are no strings.

642
00:54:51,833 --> 00:54:53,700
That's right, Robert.

643
00:54:53,767 --> 00:54:56,633
Not on these puppets.

644
00:54:56,700 --> 00:54:58,867
How do you
make them?

645
00:54:58,933 --> 00:55:00,333
Well, I have
a confession to make.

646
00:55:00,400 --> 00:55:01,933
I didn't make them.

647
00:55:02,067 --> 00:55:04,700
I bought them
at an auction
years ago.

648
00:55:04,767 --> 00:55:05,867
They came
in an old trunk,

649
00:55:05,933 --> 00:55:07,733
and when I took
them home, well,

650
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:10,300
they were the same then
as they are now.

651
00:55:10,367 --> 00:55:12,367
See, I've tried
to duplicate
their process,

652
00:55:12,433 --> 00:55:14,567
but I've never been able
to make a living puppet.

653
00:55:14,633 --> 00:55:19,933
I've come close.
Heaven knows
I've come close.

654
00:55:20,067 --> 00:55:23,067
Mm. Can't say I like
the way they're
staring at me.

655
00:55:23,133 --> 00:55:25,133
Oh, don't be fooled
by the way they look.

656
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:26,667
They're really gentle.

657
00:55:26,733 --> 00:55:33,367
Hard, fine grain.
No knots, no flaws.
Perfect wood.

658
00:55:33,433 --> 00:55:34,667
I've never seen wood
like it.

659
00:55:34,733 --> 00:55:36,067
Mm-hmm.

660
00:55:36,067 --> 00:55:37,533
What is it?

661
00:55:37,600 --> 00:55:40,200
Very exotic,
very expensive.

662
00:55:40,267 --> 00:55:44,467
And here, here are
the tools you'll need.

663
00:55:44,533 --> 00:55:46,233
Study them.

664
00:55:46,300 --> 00:55:47,867
Learn what each one
can do.

665
00:55:52,967 --> 00:55:56,067
444 pieces.

666
00:55:56,067 --> 00:55:59,733
Each piece must be
cut precisely
to scale

667
00:55:59,800 --> 00:56:02,133
like the inner gears
of a wooden clock.

668
00:56:02,200 --> 00:56:04,333
There can be
no flaws,
no mistakes

669
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:06,967
in size, dimension,
or shape.

670
00:56:07,067 --> 00:56:10,633
Otherwise,
the puppet cannot be
properly assembled.

671
00:56:10,700 --> 00:56:13,467
All this
would be wasted.

672
00:56:13,533 --> 00:56:15,400
What will it look like
when it's finished?

673
00:56:15,467 --> 00:56:19,067
You'll learn that
in good time, son.

674
00:56:19,100 --> 00:56:20,133
I don't understand.

675
00:56:20,200 --> 00:56:23,067
I mean, what...
What's the secret?

676
00:56:23,067 --> 00:56:24,767
These are just
pieces of wood.

677
00:56:24,833 --> 00:56:26,767
No matter how perfect
I carve them,

678
00:56:26,833 --> 00:56:30,367
they'll still just be
pieces of wood.

679
00:56:30,433 --> 00:56:34,433
How can putting them
together make them live?

680
00:56:34,500 --> 00:56:35,567
You want to know
the secret

681
00:56:35,633 --> 00:56:38,867
of how to make
a dead thing live?

682
00:56:38,933 --> 00:56:43,100
You put your soul
into it.

683
00:56:43,167 --> 00:56:46,200
You put everything
you have into this
carving,

684
00:56:46,267 --> 00:56:51,933
and you have
my word,
it will live.

685
00:56:52,067 --> 00:56:54,367
Toulon: Fate always steps in

686
00:56:54,433 --> 00:56:56,700
in form of those who think
brute strength

687
00:56:56,767 --> 00:56:58,533
is a match for brains.

688
00:56:58,600 --> 00:57:01,633
All my puppets,
they will always avenge a wrong

689
00:57:01,700 --> 00:57:04,267
against their protectors.

690
00:57:04,333 --> 00:57:06,500
[Thunder]

691
00:57:41,300 --> 00:57:43,133
Hey. Get the hell
out of here!

692
00:57:43,200 --> 00:57:44,267
Keep it down, honey.

693
00:57:44,333 --> 00:57:46,133
We don't want to
wake the house,
do we?

694
00:57:46,200 --> 00:57:47,933
[Growling]

695
00:57:48,067 --> 00:57:48,967
What the hell?

696
00:57:49,067 --> 00:57:51,133
Aah!

697
00:57:51,200 --> 00:57:53,067
[Pinhead growling]

698
00:57:53,133 --> 00:57:55,300
[Thunder]

699
00:58:13,067 --> 00:58:14,700
Go, go, Robert.

700
00:58:22,700 --> 00:58:25,267
Robert, get her
in the house.

701
00:58:25,333 --> 00:58:27,267
Go on. Get her
in there now.

702
00:58:44,400 --> 00:58:46,567
[Growling]

703
00:59:02,100 --> 00:59:05,133
That's right.
Do it, bitch.

704
00:59:05,200 --> 00:59:07,900
I said, do it.
Oh, yeah. That's right.

705
00:59:07,967 --> 00:59:09,700
Oh, yeah.
You like that, don't you?

706
00:59:09,767 --> 00:59:11,933
[Puppets growling]

707
00:59:18,667 --> 00:59:20,833
[Grunting]

708
00:59:31,833 --> 00:59:33,233
Heh heh heh!

709
01:00:16,100 --> 01:00:18,267
[Grunting]

710
01:00:33,000 --> 01:00:35,133
Aah!

711
01:00:36,267 --> 01:00:38,433
[Groaning]

712
01:00:40,533 --> 01:00:42,700
[Screaming]

713
01:00:59,433 --> 01:01:01,667
[Groaning]

714
01:01:32,967 --> 01:01:34,467
I did it.

715
01:01:41,800 --> 01:01:42,967
No.

716
01:01:45,667 --> 01:01:48,567
No, please.

717
01:01:48,633 --> 01:01:51,200
[Growls]

718
01:01:51,267 --> 01:01:53,267
See, you don't
understand.

719
01:01:57,067 --> 01:01:59,067
Hee hee hee!

720
01:02:02,933 --> 01:02:06,467
Please. Please.
Don't you understand?

721
01:02:08,967 --> 01:02:11,367
Hee hee hee!

722
01:02:15,967 --> 01:02:18,633
It can't be stopped now.
It's too late.

723
01:02:21,133 --> 01:02:23,100
Unh!

724
01:02:24,933 --> 01:02:28,900
I... please.
You don't understand.

725
01:02:28,967 --> 01:02:31,567
All I've done
I've done for you.

726
01:02:31,633 --> 01:02:34,367
Aah!

727
01:02:34,433 --> 01:02:35,633
Please.

728
01:02:39,800 --> 01:02:43,667
Don't make me
hurt you, please.

729
01:02:43,733 --> 01:02:45,233
Aah!

730
01:02:51,933 --> 01:02:54,300
What are you doing?

731
01:02:54,367 --> 01:02:55,633
I beg you.

732
01:02:55,700 --> 01:03:00,800
All that I've done,
all that I've created,

733
01:03:00,867 --> 01:03:03,600
I've done it for you.

734
01:03:03,667 --> 01:03:08,600
No! No! Aah! Aah!
No, blade, no!

735
01:03:08,667 --> 01:03:10,833
[Screaming]

736
01:03:53,533 --> 01:03:55,367
Oh, my god!
Oh, my god!

737
01:03:55,433 --> 01:03:58,533
What have you done?

738
01:03:58,600 --> 01:04:01,433
You see?

739
01:04:01,500 --> 01:04:04,267
I did it.

740
01:04:04,333 --> 01:04:05,733
I did it.

741
01:04:18,533 --> 01:04:22,967
Robert, no!

742
01:04:23,067 --> 01:04:25,200
[Screaming]

743
01:04:28,067 --> 01:04:30,200
Toulon: Greed, envy,
and power killed my enemies,

744
01:04:30,267 --> 01:04:31,267
not the puppets.

745
01:04:31,333 --> 01:04:32,767
My experiments continue,

746
01:04:32,833 --> 01:04:34,767
and so do my wooden creations,

747
01:04:34,833 --> 01:04:37,067
but their secret
is not for the timid.

748
01:04:37,100 --> 01:04:39,067
They have the ability
to live forever,

749
01:04:39,133 --> 01:04:40,467
and you can live
through them

750
01:04:40,533 --> 01:04:43,367
if you have the desire,
the will to do it.

751
01:04:43,433 --> 01:04:45,300
If you let no one
stand in your way

752
01:04:45,367 --> 01:04:48,067
and devote your life
to their existence,

753
01:04:48,067 --> 01:04:49,333
you can be a puppet master.

754
01:04:49,400 --> 01:04:52,767
The ultimate power is yours
for the taking.

755
01:04:52,833 --> 01:04:54,800
You'll never control
those creatures!

756
01:04:54,867 --> 01:04:56,833
They're mine!

757
01:04:56,900 --> 01:04:59,600
You fool.
That's not
what I want.

758
01:04:59,667 --> 01:05:01,767
Don't you
understand?

759
01:05:01,833 --> 01:05:05,467
Your little friends
brought Andre toulon
back to life.

760
01:05:23,633 --> 01:05:25,800
[Scraping]

761
01:06:37,767 --> 01:06:39,800
He wasn't some
benevolent soul.

762
01:06:39,867 --> 01:06:42,067
He was a psychopath!

763
01:06:42,133 --> 01:06:43,400
Don't you know how
he spent

764
01:06:43,467 --> 01:06:45,933
the last days
of his life
right here

765
01:06:46,067 --> 01:06:47,767
in this very hotel?

766
01:06:50,133 --> 01:06:55,100
Tonight, we take up
residence

767
01:06:55,167 --> 01:06:59,300
in our permanent
new bodies.

768
01:07:15,667 --> 01:07:17,500
To us.

769
01:07:23,200 --> 01:07:25,367
[Chanting foreign language]

770
01:07:58,367 --> 01:07:59,533
[Gasps]

771
01:08:27,067 --> 01:08:30,133
[Toulon's voice]
You see how easy
it can be?

772
01:08:30,200 --> 01:08:32,533
Only a moment
of pain,

773
01:08:32,600 --> 01:08:35,600
and then
immortality.

774
01:08:35,667 --> 01:08:38,400
All will soon
be glorious.

775
01:08:38,467 --> 01:08:40,600
[Gasps]

776
01:08:40,667 --> 01:08:44,433
[Grunting]

777
01:08:44,500 --> 01:08:46,267
You filthy schwein!

778
01:08:46,333 --> 01:08:48,833
You brought me
animal brains!

779
01:08:48,900 --> 01:08:52,533
Animal brains. Ohh.

780
01:08:52,600 --> 01:08:55,233
I'll just have to make
the best of it.

781
01:08:59,233 --> 01:09:02,133
You see, I must
keep my promise
to Elsa.

782
01:09:02,200 --> 01:09:04,867
Your hard work
has not been in vain.

783
01:09:04,933 --> 01:09:08,267
Of course, you may
wither into dry wood,

784
01:09:08,333 --> 01:09:11,867
but you've given me
back my wife.

785
01:09:11,933 --> 01:09:13,067
Man: Coward!

786
01:09:13,133 --> 01:09:16,300
Here, Michael! Here!

787
01:09:22,500 --> 01:09:24,967
Hurry!

788
01:09:25,067 --> 01:09:26,900
Are you still
afraid?

789
01:09:29,067 --> 01:09:32,600
But we must make
you drink,
sweet fräulein.

790
01:09:39,700 --> 01:09:42,567
We cannot waste
our fuel, mein frau.

791
01:09:42,633 --> 01:09:45,767
Only a single
goblet remains.

792
01:09:51,100 --> 01:09:53,467
Stay back,
you fool!

793
01:09:59,900 --> 01:10:02,300
Come back with that!

794
01:10:02,367 --> 01:10:04,167
Aah!

795
01:10:14,600 --> 01:10:16,467
[Groaning]

796
01:10:16,533 --> 01:10:18,067
Woman: Michael!

797
01:10:24,600 --> 01:10:26,433
Toulon: Elsa, stop!

798
01:10:26,500 --> 01:10:29,067
Come back to me!

799
01:10:29,133 --> 01:10:31,300
[Groaning]

800
01:10:42,333 --> 01:10:43,633
Ugh!

801
01:10:58,467 --> 01:11:00,467
Ohh, ohh.

802
01:11:10,600 --> 01:11:12,767
[Puppets growling]

803
01:11:22,633 --> 01:11:24,800
[Toulon whimpering]

804
01:11:26,067 --> 01:11:28,200
[Screaming]

805
01:11:48,067 --> 01:11:51,767
He began his final
experiment,

806
01:11:51,833 --> 01:11:54,200
soul transference.

807
01:11:54,267 --> 01:11:55,867
I'm not here
for the secret

808
01:11:55,933 --> 01:11:58,600
of bringing these
puppets to life.

809
01:11:58,667 --> 01:12:03,167
I want to know
what makes them
die for good.

810
01:12:08,700 --> 01:12:11,333
Damn fool.

811
01:12:11,400 --> 01:12:13,300
I was sent here
for the secret

812
01:12:13,367 --> 01:12:16,900
by the creatures
toulon left behind,

813
01:12:16,967 --> 01:12:22,333
immortals,
souls trapped
in wooden bodies,

814
01:12:22,400 --> 01:12:25,700
living every day
in agony.

815
01:12:25,767 --> 01:12:30,533
All they want is
revenge on their
puppet master,

816
01:12:30,600 --> 01:12:33,200
and now that's you.

817
01:12:33,267 --> 01:12:35,933
Congratulations
on your legacy.

